The paper discusses the use of machine learning methods for dialogue modelling, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The methods used are data-driven and involve reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian processes, which is a statistical method, and therefore could be categorized under statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of dialogue systems in facilitating human-computer interaction, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
